{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "leads-marketing-site-2026",
    "name": "006 LEADS_MARKETING_SITE",
    "description": "All public /leads/* surface consumed by the vianda-home marketing site. Organized by frontend consumer (one collection per consumer), not per endpoint group.\n\nFolders:\n- Zipcode metrics (no auth, no reCAPTCHA) \u2014 navbar coverage probe.\n- Country selectors (no auth, no reCAPTCHA) \u2014 /leads/countries, /leads/supplier-countries with ETag + 304 + long Cache-Control.\n- country_code contract \u2014 /leads/plans, /leads/restaurants, /leads/featured-restaurant (required \u2192 400; unsupported \u2192 [] or null, 200).\n- Admin override on market status (guardrails) \u2014 PUT /admin/markets/{id} activation/deactivation rules. Requires super admin.\n\nContracts:\n- docs/api/marketing_site/LEADS_COVERAGE_CHECKER.md\n- docs/api/b2c_client/feedback_from_client/RESTAURANTS_BY_ZIPCODE.md\n- Cron follow-up: docs/plans/market-status-cron.md\n\nShared auth: Login Super Admin is idempotent \u2014 if `superAdminAuthToken` is already set as a Postman global (e.g. via Newman --globals from a seed run), the login request is skipped. See docs/postman/guidelines/LEADS_COLLECTION_CONVENTIONS.md.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Zipcode metrics (no auth, no reCAPTCHA)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET zipcode-metrics (zip + country_code)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200 or 404 if endpoint not implemented', function () {",
                  "    const code = pm.response.code;",
                  "    pm.expect([200, 404]).to.include(code);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.test('Response has requested_zipcode', function () { pm.expect(body).to.have.property('requested_zipcode'); });",
                  "    pm.test('Response has matched_zipcode', function () { pm.expect(body).to.have.property('matched_zipcode'); });",
                  "    pm.test('Response has restaurant_count', function () { pm.expect(body).to.have.property('restaurant_count'); });",
                  "    pm.test('Response has has_coverage', function () { pm.expect(body).to.have.property('has_coverage'); });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/leads/zipcode-metrics?zip={{sampleZip}}&country_code={{sampleCountryCode}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "leads", "zipcode-metrics"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "zip", "value": "{{sampleZip}}" },
                { "key": "country_code", "value": "{{sampleCountryCode}}" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Lead flow: get metrics for a zipcode. No auth. Rate-limited per IP (e.g. 60/min); 429 when exceeded."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET zipcode-metrics (zip only, default country)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
